detaileddescription.para:
Adding this macro to your logic will allow the failing test to be considered passing, example: ZTEST_EXPECT_FAIL(my_suite, test_x);
ZTEST(my_suite, text_x) {
  zassert_true(false, NULL);
}


_suite_name



The name of the suite 




_test_name



The name of the test

Adding this macro to your logic will allow the failing test to be considered passing, example: ZTEST_EXPECT_SKIP(my_suite, test_x);
ZTEST(my_suite, text_x) {
  zassume_true(false, NULL);
}


_suite_name



The name of the suite 




_test_name



The name of the test
